@startuml C4_Quality_Invariants
!include https://raw.githubusercontent.com/plantuml-stdlib/C4-PlantUML/master/C4_Component.puml

title YAWL Quality Gate - Q-Invariants Validation

Boundary(code, "Code") {
    Component(impl_code, "Implementation Code", "Java", "Real implementations")
}

Boundary(invariant_checks, "Q-Invariant Checks") {
    Component(real_impl_check, "RealImplementationChecker", "Validation", "Not mock/stub")
    Component(exception_thrower, "ExceptionThrower", "Validation", "Throws on error")
    Component(no_lie_check, "NoLieChecker", "Validation", "Code = docs")
    Component(no_fallback_check, "NoFallbackChecker", "Validation", "No silent degradation")
}

Boundary(invariant_rules, "Invariant Rules") {
    Component(rule1, "Rule 1: real_impl ∨ throw", "Logic", "Must be real or throw")
    Component(rule2, "Rule 2: ¬mock ∧ ¬stub", "Logic", "No fakes allowed")
    Component(rule3, "Rule 3: ¬silent_fallback", "Logic", "No degradation")
    Component(rule4, "Rule 4: code matches docs", "Logic", "Be truthful")
}

Boundary(validation_engine_q, "Validation Engine") {
    Component(invariant_validator, "InvariantValidator", "Orchestrator", "Runs all checks")
    Component(receipt_q, "InvariantReceipt", "Report", "JSON report")
}

Boundary(gates_q, "Gates") {
    Component(pass_gate_q, "PASS", "Green", "All invariants hold")
    Component(fail_gate_q, "FAIL", "Red", "Violations found")
}

impl_code --> real_impl_check: Validates
impl_code --> exception_thrower: Validates
impl_code --> no_lie_check: Validates
impl_code --> no_fallback_check: Validates

rule1 --> real_impl_check: Implements
rule2 --> exception_thrower: Implements
rule3 --> no_fallback_check: Implements
rule4 --> no_lie_check: Implements

real_impl_check --> invariant_validator: Reports
exception_thrower --> invariant_validator: Reports
no_lie_check --> invariant_validator: Reports
no_fallback_check --> invariant_validator: Reports

invariant_validator --> receipt_q: Generates
receipt_q --> pass_gate_q: All valid
receipt_q --> fail_gate_q: Violations found

Note as N1
Q-Invariants enforce "real code" principle
Rules:
1. real_impl ∨ throw - Must be real implementation or throw exception
2. ¬mock ∧ ¬stub - No mocks/stubs allowed
3. ¬silent_fallback - No silent degradation
4. code matches docs - Documentation must match code

Invalid:
❌ return "default"
❌ log.error() instead of throw
❌ catch and return null

Valid:
✅ Real implementation
✅ throw new UnsupportedOperationException()
✅ Documentation matches
End note

SHOW_LEGEND()
@enduml
